      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "IFTIHAR (2) looks nicely placed. Two runs to date have netted two minor placings, sent out big odds in a handy maiden here last time when giving a good sight, beaten under a length. She'll be better again and take plenty of running down. SAVANNAH QUEEN (5) found the line nicely on debut at Pakenham over 1200m, getting home late into fourth. She'll relish the extra ground here and does fare better at the barriers. Expect she goes close. KOKORO TIME (3) debuted in a stronger race at Caulfield Heath and was largely outclassed but should be an improver off that. This suits better and up in trip from a good gate helps. PARVENU (4) next best.",
